    Let <fr:tex>K</fr:tex> be a complex of cosimplicial sheaves on <fr:tex>S</fr:tex>, endowed with an increasing filtration <fr:tex>W</fr:tex>.
    We define the <fr:em>diagonal filtration</fr:em> <fr:tex>\delta (W,L)</fr:tex> of <fr:tex>W</fr:tex> and <fr:tex>L</fr:tex> to be the increasing filtration of <fr:tex>\mathrm {s} K</fr:tex> given by

    <fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="false"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2371</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:addr>hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6.1</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6.1.xml</fr:route><fr:number>7.1.6.1</fr:number><fr:parent>hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex
display="block">         \begin {aligned}           \delta (W,L)_n(\mathrm {s} K)           &amp;= \bigoplus _{p,q} W_{n+p}(K^{p,q})         \\&amp;= \sum _p \mathrm {s}(W_{n+p}(K)) \cap  L^p(\mathrm {s} K).         \end {aligned}       \tag{7.1.6.1}       </fr:tex></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:p><fr:p>
    We have

    <fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="false"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2372</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:addr>hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6.2</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6.2.xml</fr:route><fr:number>7.1.6.2</fr:number><fr:parent>hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex
display="block">         \operatorname {Gr}_n^{\delta (W,L)}(\mathrm {s} K)         \simeq  \bigoplus _p \operatorname {Gr}_{n+p}^W(K^{\bullet  p})[-p].       \tag{7.1.6.2}       </fr:tex></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:p><fr:p>
    The functor <fr:tex>(K,W)\mapsto (\mathrm {s} K,\delta (W,L))</fr:tex> sends filtered quasi-isomorphisms to filtered quasi-isomorphisms, and defines

    <fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="false"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2373</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:addr>hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6.3</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6.3.xml</fr:route><fr:number>7.1.6.3</fr:number><fr:parent>hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex
display="block">         \begin {aligned}           (s,\delta )           \colon  \mathrm {D}^+\mathrm {F}(S_\bullet )           &amp;\to  \mathrm {D}^+\mathrm {F}(S)         \\(K,W)           &amp;\mapsto  (\mathrm {s} K,\delta (W,L))         \end {aligned}       \tag{7.1.6.3}       </fr:tex></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>

    whence, by composition with <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-iii-7.1.5.1"
href="hodge-theory-iii-7.1.5.1.xml"
taxon="Equation"
number="7.1.5.1"></fr:ref>,

    <fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="false"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2374</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:addr>hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6.4</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6.4.xml</fr:route><fr:number>7.1.6.4</fr:number><fr:parent>hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex
display="block">         \begin {aligned}           (\mathrm {R}\Gamma ,\delta (-,L))           \colon  \mathrm {D}^+\mathrm {F}(X_\bullet )           &amp;\to  \mathrm {D}^+\mathrm {F}(S)         \\(K,W)           &amp;\mapsto  (\mathrm {R}\Gamma  K,\delta (W,L)).         \end {aligned}       \tag{7.1.6.4}       </fr:tex></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>

    From <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6.2"
href="hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6.2.xml"
taxon="Equation"
number="7.1.6.2"></fr:ref>, we see that

    <fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="false"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2375</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:addr>hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6.5</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6.5.xml</fr:route><fr:number>7.1.6.5</fr:number><fr:parent>hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex
display="block">         \operatorname {Gr}_n^{\delta (W,L)}         = \bigoplus _p \mathrm {R}{a_p}_*(\operatorname {Gr}_{n+p}^W K)[-p].       \tag{7.1.6.5}       </fr:tex></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:context><fr:related></fr:related><fr:backlinks></fr:backlinks><fr:references></fr:references></fr:backmatter></fr:tree>